This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as document-level relation extraction. Additionally, the use of pre-trained language models like BERT is a common technique in this sub-category. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with machine learning models and their application to a specific task. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of a pre-trained language model to improve the performance of a machine learning task. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with extracting relations between entities in a document, which is a common task in information retrieval. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks to improve the performance of a natural language processing task.
